WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.135 --> 00:00:03.694
<i>Previously on</i> The Following:

2
00:00:04.171 --> 00:00:07.073
<i>Serial killer Joe Carroll
has escaped from prison.</i>

3
00:00:07.241 --> 00:00:08.368
Get some help now!

4
00:00:08.542 --> 00:00:11.942
<i>Things didn't end well with the
Bureau. but you caught Carroll.</i>

5
00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:13.892
<i>- No one knows him like you.</i>
- I'm not an agent.

6
00:00:14.014 --> 00:00:17.246
He cut out his victim's
eyes as a nod to Poe.

7
00:00:17.417 --> 00:00:20.410
He didn't just eviscerate female
students. he was making art.

8
00:00:20.587 --> 00:00:22.055
Sarah was his unfinished work.

9
00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:26.284
- He wanted to get the ending right.
- The point of Sarah's death was for you.

10
00:00:26.460 --> 00:00:28.691
He's finding people.
They're his followers.

11
00:00:28.862 --> 00:00:32.299
Prison guard. Gay neighbors. How
do they figure into your new plot?

12
00:00:32.466 --> 00:00:35.368
- We know about the cult.
- I think of them as my friends.

13
00:00:35.536 --> 00:00:36.868
What's my sequel about. Joe?

14
00:00:37.037 --> 00:00:40.701
We're gonna write this together. Ryan.
even though you slept with my wife.

15
00:00:40.874 --> 00:00:42.674
- She show you the letter?
- How does he know?

16
00:00:42.743 --> 00:00:44.075
He doesn't. No one needs to.

17
00:00:44.244 --> 00:00:47.544
Mom. What's going
on? It's Dad. isn't it?

18
00:00:47.714 --> 00:00:50.047
- I didn't know what to say.
- If this book ends...

19
00:00:50.217 --> 00:00:52.498
with anything other than
your death. plan on a rewrite.

20
00:00:54.254 --> 00:00:56.052
Joey? Where is he? Joey?

21
00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:57.418
Joey. where are you?

22
00:00:57.591 --> 00:00:59.423
Where's Denise? Where's my son?

23
00:01:00.594 --> 00:01:02.563
Sorry. didn't mean to scare you.

24
00:01:02.763 --> 00:01:03.992
Is everything okay?

25
00:01:04.164 --> 00:01:05.444
Extra patrol this evening.

26
00:01:05.599 --> 00:01:07.761
I thought they caught
him. Saw it on the news.

27
00:01:07.935 --> 00:01:10.268
Still. mind if I check
your doors and windows?

28
00:01:10.437 --> 00:01:11.871
Sure.

29
00:01:13.907 --> 00:01:16.502
Come on in. I think
everyone's asleep.

30
00:01:19.780 --> 00:01:22.113
Why don't we start upstairs?

31
00:01:26.620 --> 00:01:28.145
Do you want me to wake everyone?

32
00:01:28.322 --> 00:01:32.157
No. we don't wanna do that.
Let's start with the room on the end.

33
00:01:32.326 --> 00:01:33.385
Okay.

34
00:01:41.034 --> 00:01:43.094
This is Jesse's room. She's out.

35
00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:45.830
Yes. Jesse's room. I know.

36
00:01:48.709 --> 00:01:50.940
I've studied this house a lot.

37
00:02:01.955 --> 00:02:02.979
What is that?

38
00:02:04.224 --> 00:02:06.955
I threw this up here earlier.

39
00:02:07.361 --> 00:02:12.561
It's my kit. It's important
to have the right tools.

40
00:02:15.869 --> 00:02:18.168
I've been planning
this for a long time.

41
00:02:25.379 --> 00:02:27.905
<i>Serial killer Joe Carroll
has been captured...</i>

42
00:02:28.081 --> 00:02:30.550
<i>held at Richmond
Federal Detention Center.</i>

43
00:02:30.717 --> 00:02:32.709
<i>As of early this
morning. Carroll's son...</i>

44
00:02:32.886 --> 00:02:36.550
<i>Joey Matthews. and his nanny.
Denise Harris. have been missing.</i>

45
00:02:36.723 --> 00:02:39.887
<i>An AMBER Alert is in effect
and we ask that anyone...</i>

46
00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:43.895
<i>with any information as to their
whereabouts. please contact the FBI.</i>

47
00:02:44.331 --> 00:02:46.425
What's going on.
Ryan? Where's my son?

48
00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:49.593
- We need to talk.
- Why is Joe doing this?

49
00:02:49.770 --> 00:02:53.229
I don't understand how Denise is
involved. Are they going to hurt Joey?

50
00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:55.736
I think she's your
nanny because of Joe.

51
00:02:55.909 --> 00:02:58.378
- I think he put her here...
- No. that's impossible.

52
00:02:58.545 --> 00:03:02.209
She's been Joey's nanny for two
years. She lives with me. I know her.

53
00:03:02.482 --> 00:03:06.852
The accomplices that helped him
kill Sarah Fuller were there for years...

54
00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:09.353
using false identities.
We think she did too.

55
00:03:09.523 --> 00:03:13.255
I did a background check. I checked
her references. I have records.

56
00:03:13.427 --> 00:03:15.419
- Can I see them?
- Yeah.

57
00:03:20.867 --> 00:03:23.894
Traces of Zolpidem on the
counter. She drugged the guards.

58
00:03:24.071 --> 00:03:27.132
- I bet the kid too.
- Carried him down to the garage.

59
00:03:27.307 --> 00:03:31.210
Her car was found 10 minutes ago
in a parking lot 45 minutes from here.

60
00:03:36.583 --> 00:03:41.112
Denise Harris from Alexandria. Her
address. her references. it's all there.

61
00:03:41.288 --> 00:03:44.156
She talked about her mom
a lot. I guess they were close.

62
00:03:44.324 --> 00:03:45.724
No dad in the picture.

63
00:03:45.892 --> 00:03:48.088
Ever meet her friends
or overhear phone calls?

64
00:03:48.261 --> 00:03:51.789
Her friends never came over.
She was shy. she kept to herself.

65
00:03:51.965 --> 00:03:55.231
She read in her room a lot.

66
00:03:56.636 --> 00:03:58.070
I can't be this blind. can I?

67
00:03:58.238 --> 00:04:00.639
You cannot afford to
think like that. Understand?

68
00:04:03.143 --> 00:04:04.577
Find my son.

69
00:04:17.491 --> 00:04:18.686
Can't run from me!

70
00:04:28.835 --> 00:04:30.861
I got you.

71
00:04:31.838 --> 00:04:33.431
Look at this place.

72
00:04:40.313 --> 00:04:41.804
Wow!

73
00:04:42.315 --> 00:04:43.339
Whose house is this?

74
00:04:43.784 --> 00:04:46.049
- Friend of a friend.
- It's okay that we're here?

75
00:04:46.219 --> 00:04:47.380
Yeah.

76
00:04:47.587 --> 00:04:49.385
Come on. let's check it out.

77
00:04:51.324 --> 00:04:52.986
Can I call my mom now?

78
00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:58.792
Honey. told you. your
mom told us not to call.

79
00:04:59.232 --> 00:05:01.633
She doesn't want anyone
to know where we are.

80
00:05:02.002 --> 00:05:03.561
Remember what I said?

81
00:05:03.737 --> 00:05:05.365
- We're on an adventure.
- Mm-hmm.

82
00:05:06.339 --> 00:05:07.739
Come on.

83
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.000
What's wrong with you?

84
00:05:11.178 --> 00:05:12.544
- I hate kids.
- Stop it.

85
00:05:12.712 --> 00:05:17.207
- I do. I hate talking to them. I hate looking...
- Not this kid. Okay?

86
00:05:17.384 --> 00:05:18.852
You like this kid.

87
00:05:19.019 --> 00:05:21.352
Just keep saying
it until it sticks.

88
00:05:21.521 --> 00:05:23.319
I'd rather snap his neck.

89
00:05:25.759 --> 00:05:27.352
I'm kidding.

90
00:05:31.865 --> 00:05:33.197
- Is there a problem?
- Nope.

91
00:05:33.366 --> 00:05:34.390
No. not here.

92
00:05:34.568 --> 00:05:36.366
We're on an
adventure with a kid.

93
00:05:36.536 --> 00:05:39.938
And I like kids.
Especially this kid.

94
00:05:45.712 --> 00:05:47.510
What was that about?

95
00:05:47.848 --> 00:05:49.783
It's been a long night.

96
00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:51.879
He's tired.

97
00:05:59.893 --> 00:06:01.657
It's good to have you back.

98
00:06:04.297 --> 00:06:05.641
<i>Developments from Richmond...</i>

99
00:06:05.665 --> 00:06:07.429
<i>Virginia upon Sarah
Fuller's death...</i>

100
00:06:07.601 --> 00:06:10.196
<i>as the search for young
Joey Matthews continues.</i>

101
00:06:10.370 --> 00:06:13.704
<i>Serial killer Joe Carroll's son is
believed to have been abducted...</i>

102
00:06:13.874 --> 00:06:18.039
Team over there is covering ground search.
That group is on our prison guard. Jordy...

103
00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:19.804
and we got Joey's search here.

104
00:06:19.980 --> 00:06:21.915
This is Agent Mitchell.
Cyber Forensics.

105
00:06:22.082 --> 00:06:23.812
From our D.C. office.
She's awesome.

106
00:06:24.217 --> 00:06:26.413
- Nice to meet you.
- Where are we on the nanny?

107
00:06:26.586 --> 00:06:30.489
I know Denise Harris is not from Alexandria
because Denise Harris does not exist.

108
00:06:30.690 --> 00:06:33.125
We ID'd Sarah Fuller's
gay or not-so-gay neighbors.

109
00:06:33.293 --> 00:06:35.558
Real names are Jacob
Wells and Paul Torres.

110
00:06:35.729 --> 00:06:38.722
Jacob is from Lake Whitehurst.
Paul is from El Paso. Texas.

111
00:06:38.899 --> 00:06:42.063
Where he's a computer consultant with
a history of fraud. Explains the fake IDs.

112
00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:43.760
Where's Agent Mason?

113
00:06:51.478 --> 00:06:53.743
I'd just get rid of
him. Send him home.

114
00:06:53.914 --> 00:06:55.712
Can't. It's part of the story.

115
00:06:55.882 --> 00:06:57.326
Then sideline him
before he cracks.

116
00:06:57.350 --> 00:07:02.084
Because he will crack. You
weren't around 10 years ago. I lived it.

117
00:07:05.492 --> 00:07:08.587
Well. this is awkward.

118
00:07:09.095 --> 00:07:12.259
Hello. Mr. Hardy. I'm Agent
Debra Parker. I'm new to the party.

119
00:07:12.766 --> 00:07:16.430
We were just. uh.
discussing you.

120
00:07:16.603 --> 00:07:18.663
Parker's from Quantico.
She's taking lead.

121
00:07:18.838 --> 00:07:21.364
- May I speak to Mr. Hardy privately...
- Where's Mason?

122
00:07:21.541 --> 00:07:22.873
On her way back to Quantico.

123
00:07:23.043 --> 00:07:25.638
She put a former agent in
a room with Joe Carroll...

124
00:07:25.812 --> 00:07:29.806
and let him break three of his
fingers. Turns out that's a no-no.

125
00:07:30.383 --> 00:07:32.978
- Three. huh?
- Turner thinks I should dismiss you.

126
00:07:33.153 --> 00:07:35.884
He remembers you for who
you were 10 years ago. not now.

127
00:07:36.056 --> 00:07:38.651
- And there's a difference?
- I hope so...

128
00:07:38.825 --> 00:07:42.284
because Carroll has cast you as
a main character in his sequel...

129
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:44.397
so I can't just kick
you to the curb.

130
00:07:46.499 --> 00:07:48.468
I'm sorry about Sarah Fuller.

131
00:07:49.803 --> 00:07:50.827
I want a gun.

132
00:07:51.504 --> 00:07:54.838
I'm not asking to be an agent.
but deputize me and give me a gun.

133
00:07:55.008 --> 00:07:57.068
When was the last
time you had a drink?

134
00:07:57.277 --> 00:08:01.180
Director Franklin asked me to be here
and if I'm going to stay. I want a gun.

135
00:08:01.348 --> 00:08:02.816
I'll take it under advisement.

136
00:08:02.983 --> 00:08:05.578
How's your heart? I see you
suffer from cardiomyopathy.

137
00:08:05.785 --> 00:08:08.653
Is this the best use of our
time? There's a child missing.

138
00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:11.291
So tell me about
Carroll's accomplices.

139
00:08:14.594 --> 00:08:18.554
He used this prison guard to gain access
to the Internet to create a following.

140
00:08:18.932 --> 00:08:22.061
- Like a cult.
- Let's not use that. People don't hear it well.

141
00:08:22.235 --> 00:08:24.704
Call it what you want.
but people do his bidding.

142
00:08:24.871 --> 00:08:26.601
Carroll mentioned a letter.

143
00:08:32.712 --> 00:08:37.741
Claire Matthews received a letter a week
before Carroll's escape. It was personal.

144
00:08:39.919 --> 00:08:43.356
- He questioned our relationship.
- As did the FBI eight years ago.

145
00:08:45.091 --> 00:08:46.957
So now you're up to speed.

146
00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:50.387
We got more bodies.

147
00:08:53.066 --> 00:08:56.867
Blood smear. Jordy was
messy. left prints everywhere.

148
00:08:57.037 --> 00:08:58.835
No attempt to
conceal his identity.

149
00:08:59.239 --> 00:09:01.538
Victim number three.
She tried to run...

150
00:09:01.975 --> 00:09:04.342
quick struggle. not
the case for the others.

151
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:14.815
Nine girls in the house at the time.
Some woke up when they heard screams...

152
00:09:14.988 --> 00:09:16.047
and Jordy ran.

153
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:20.125
- He removed the eyes. Carroll's signature.
- Is Jordy playing Poe's greatest hits?

154
00:09:20.293 --> 00:09:23.821
Playing an homage to Carroll.
Following in the footsteps of his hero.

155
00:09:23.997 --> 00:09:26.159
It's ceremonial. The
work of an acolyte.

156
00:09:26.366 --> 00:09:29.165
Let's not use that word
either. It implies the other word.

157
00:09:29.369 --> 00:09:30.997
Let's say "Carroll's
accomplices."

158
00:09:31.171 --> 00:09:35.336
Pick a word. any word. but
this is mind control at work.

159
00:09:35.508 --> 00:09:38.000
- Why have his son kidnapped?
- A biblical offering.

160
00:09:38.178 --> 00:09:42.343
They think of him as a son of
God. Something to be worshiped.

161
00:09:42.515 --> 00:09:43.915
Or sacrificed.

162
00:09:44.517 --> 00:09:46.179
Carroll knows where the kid is.

163
00:09:46.386 --> 00:09:49.788
- He's not going to tell us.
- But he might tell his wife.

164
00:09:50.290 --> 00:09:52.452
- He asked to see her.
- He's smarter than that.

165
00:09:52.625 --> 00:09:55.754
- He's not going to tell her anything.
- Well. let's find out.

166
00:09:59.966 --> 00:10:01.662
What do I say?

167
00:10:02.302 --> 00:10:04.464
Is there anything
special I need to ask him?

168
00:10:04.637 --> 00:10:08.665
Try to engage him about Joey.
Speak to his paternal instincts.

169
00:10:09.109 --> 00:10:11.044
Make Joey important to him.

170
00:10:14.180 --> 00:10:16.206
Are you sure you wanna do this?

171
00:10:36.035 --> 00:10:37.401
I like your new place.

172
00:10:37.904 --> 00:10:40.703
Me too. How was court today?

173
00:10:40.874 --> 00:10:42.740
Moving fast. It
won't be long now.

174
00:10:42.942 --> 00:10:46.003
I can't go anymore.
I can't look at him.

175
00:10:47.947 --> 00:10:49.939
I don't ever want
to see him again.

176
00:10:52.051 --> 00:10:53.883
You don't have to.

177
00:11:33.393 --> 00:11:35.589
My hands are shaking.

178
00:11:35.762 --> 00:11:38.231
My God. you still
have that effect on me.

179
00:11:38.898 --> 00:11:41.060
- So beautiful. Always...
- Where's my son?

180
00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:49.138
- Our son. Claire.
- Please. Joe. Where is he?

181
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:54.242
Heh. do you remember
when we went to Antigua?

182
00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:57.775
We rented that little
cottage on the beach.

183
00:11:57.951 --> 00:12:01.410
We were supposed to be there for a
few days. but it turned into a month.

184
00:12:01.588 --> 00:12:03.819
I don't think we wore
clothes the entire time...

185
00:12:04.023 --> 00:12:08.518
He's growing up so fast.
Joey. He's so brilliant.

186
00:12:09.062 --> 00:12:11.497
Reading well beyond
his years. Melville. Twain.

187
00:12:11.664 --> 00:12:14.065
He finished <i>Robinson
Crusoe</i> but he didn't like it.

188
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:16.567
This must be so hard for you.

189
00:12:17.103 --> 00:12:18.537
You must feel so betrayed.

190
00:12:21.174 --> 00:12:22.665
Again.

191
00:12:24.410 --> 00:12:26.743
Come on. Claire. hang in there.

192
00:12:31.484 --> 00:12:33.783
So you got my letter.

193
00:12:33.953 --> 00:12:39.290
Is he in danger? Please. let
him be okay. Don't let him be hurt.

194
00:12:39.459 --> 00:12:41.553
I'd like some answers
to my questions.

195
00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:50.703
Tell me where Joey is first.

196
00:12:50.870 --> 00:12:54.932
I asked you some very specific
questions. I'd like you to answer them.

197
00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:58.374
- Yes.
- Yes. you what?

198
00:13:00.980 --> 00:13:04.781
Ryan and I had an affair
for almost two months.

199
00:13:08.154 --> 00:13:10.783
- After the trial.
- And the divorce.

200
00:13:10.957 --> 00:13:14.450
Oh. yes. Of course. you
waited for the divorce.

201
00:13:14.627 --> 00:13:18.826
Noble Claire. only a
proper little diddle will do.

202
00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:22.394
Was it good? The sex?

203
00:13:22.602 --> 00:13:25.902
Did your body quiver
to his every touch?

204
00:13:28.841 --> 00:13:32.141
Yes. It did.

205
00:13:32.312 --> 00:13:34.804
- We gotta get her out of there.
- Not yet.

206
00:13:36.182 --> 00:13:37.741
- The last question?
- I don't know.

207
00:13:37.917 --> 00:13:43.083
- You know the question.
- "I don't know" is my answer.

208
00:13:43.256 --> 00:13:46.317
How could I love anyone
after you? You destroyed me.

209
00:13:46.492 --> 00:13:50.691
You son of a bitch. Where's
my son? Where's Joey?

210
00:13:52.932 --> 00:13:54.423
We need to get in there! Damn!

211
00:13:54.634 --> 00:13:56.227
I will always love you.

212
00:14:18.458 --> 00:14:19.517
You okay?

213
00:14:19.692 --> 00:14:22.958
Yes. I'm sorry about
what I said in there.

214
00:14:23.896 --> 00:14:25.228
Don't be.

215
00:14:25.398 --> 00:14:28.095
- Got a car waiting...
- Is there any news on Joey?

216
00:14:29.469 --> 00:14:32.564
As soon as I know
anything. I promise...

217
00:14:33.239 --> 00:14:35.231
We're gonna find him. Claire.

218
00:14:43.316 --> 00:14:44.579
Which room do I get?

219
00:14:44.751 --> 00:14:46.913
I don't know. Let's see.

220
00:14:48.921 --> 00:14:51.982
Whoa! It's just like
my room at home.

221
00:14:52.191 --> 00:14:55.628
My Ninja Warrior!
And it's brand new!

222
00:14:55.795 --> 00:14:58.731
- How cool is that?
- Super cool.

223
00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:00.298
Can I call Mom now?

224
00:15:00.466 --> 00:15:05.803
Honey. she asked us not
to call. We have to wait.

225
00:15:05.972 --> 00:15:08.066
Why is my dad such a bad man?

226
00:15:10.510 --> 00:15:12.308
Oh. honey.

227
00:15:14.447 --> 00:15:15.847
Come here.

228
00:15:19.952 --> 00:15:21.750
Maybe...

229
00:15:22.321 --> 00:15:24.483
he's not so bad.

230
00:15:25.258 --> 00:15:27.284
Maybe we just
don't understand him.

231
00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:30.953
I'll tell you what.

232
00:15:31.330 --> 00:15:35.791
Why don't you get settled and
check out all your new things?

233
00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:44.874
<i>Good and bad no longer existed.
It was all degrees of evil now.</i>

234
00:15:45.545 --> 00:15:48.515
Gwendolyn held his dying body...

235
00:15:48.681 --> 00:15:51.674
as the storm raged on.

236
00:15:52.151 --> 00:15:58.523
Death had finally arrived.
and it was glorious to the touch.

237
00:16:05.531 --> 00:16:07.523
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

238
00:16:11.404 --> 00:16:13.430
Thank you for coming. um...

239
00:16:13.606 --> 00:16:15.165
Emma.

240
00:16:15.541 --> 00:16:16.873
I loved your book. heh.

241
00:16:17.043 --> 00:16:18.306
So you're the one.

242
00:16:18.478 --> 00:16:20.003
Emma.

243
00:16:20.513 --> 00:16:25.577
It's beautiful. All the imagery
is so vivid. I felt like I was there.

244
00:16:26.018 --> 00:16:27.179
Oh.

245
00:16:27.353 --> 00:16:28.651
You just made my day.

246
00:16:30.256 --> 00:16:32.157
Um. may I just. um...

247
00:16:36.662 --> 00:16:38.654
You have such lovely eyes. Emma.

248
00:16:38.831 --> 00:16:41.426
Don't deprive us of them. Hmm?

249
00:16:45.238 --> 00:16:46.729
Did she die? Gwendolyn?

250
00:16:46.906 --> 00:16:50.206
When she went into the sea and
started swimming to the horizon?

251
00:16:50.376 --> 00:16:51.435
Oh. you tell me.

252
00:16:52.745 --> 00:16:54.338
I think she died. heh.

253
00:16:54.514 --> 00:16:58.952
She was swimming toward
the horizon. toward the sun.

254
00:17:00.620 --> 00:17:02.748
In death. she found hope.

255
00:17:04.524 --> 00:17:06.186
Emma. hon. you almost done?

256
00:17:06.359 --> 00:17:08.123
I'm ready. Mama.

257
00:17:08.327 --> 00:17:10.762
So this is the fella
you came to see.

258
00:17:10.930 --> 00:17:13.957
My. my. I thought all writers
were big-nosed and mushy.

259
00:17:14.133 --> 00:17:15.761
- Not you.
- Mom. please. Let's go.

260
00:17:15.935 --> 00:17:20.066
I'm giving the man a compliment.
No. sir. you do not look like a writer.

261
00:17:20.239 --> 00:17:21.901
Did he sign your book?

262
00:17:22.074 --> 00:17:24.703
Oh. yes. mustn't forget this.

263
00:17:24.877 --> 00:17:29.645
"To Emma. Hopefully yours...

264
00:17:31.217 --> 00:17:32.708
Joe."

265
00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:39.783
So which is our room?

266
00:17:47.600 --> 00:17:48.795
You mean your room.

267
00:17:48.968 --> 00:17:51.062
Jacob and I are
taking the master.

268
00:17:51.237 --> 00:17:52.296
You can't do that.

269
00:17:52.471 --> 00:17:54.337
You're not gay
anymore. remember?

270
00:17:54.507 --> 00:17:58.603
We were never gay. It's
just with the kid. is that cool?

271
00:17:59.445 --> 00:18:01.380
Don't worry about it.

272
00:18:04.016 --> 00:18:06.076
<i>I tracked her through
the prison footage.</i>

273
00:18:06.252 --> 00:18:08.414
She used aliases very
similar to the gay guys.

274
00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:10.313
Three years ago.

275
00:18:11.524 --> 00:18:12.753
The guy beside her.

276
00:18:12.925 --> 00:18:14.518
Jacob Wells. You connected them.

277
00:18:14.694 --> 00:18:17.186
And get this. When I
did a search for Jacob...

278
00:18:19.599 --> 00:18:20.999
Paul Torres.

279
00:18:21.167 --> 00:18:24.262
They signed in together. You
were right. they're all in on this.

280
00:18:24.437 --> 00:18:29.000
Find the first time the nanny visited
Carroll. Maybe she didn't use an alias.

281
00:18:31.110 --> 00:18:33.705
2004. She signed
in as Emma Hill.

282
00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:38.117
Okay. there's an Emma Hill in
Petersburg. Virginia. I have an address.

283
00:18:38.284 --> 00:18:41.152
Petersburg is too close.
They'd never risk it.

284
00:18:41.320 --> 00:18:43.186
Unless they're
hiding under our nose.

285
00:18:43.356 --> 00:18:46.815
Go. take Weston. And Ryan.

286
00:18:48.961 --> 00:18:51.521
Call ahead. have the local
authorities meet you there.

287
00:19:00.706 --> 00:19:02.231
Nobody's home.

288
00:19:02.441 --> 00:19:06.037
This is the place. Neighbors say they
haven't seen anybody in a long time.

289
00:19:07.613 --> 00:19:09.411
Okay. you can't do that.

290
00:19:09.582 --> 00:19:11.380
Nope. You can't do that.

291
00:19:11.817 --> 00:19:14.946
I'm gonna check around back.
see if I can see through the window.

292
00:21:14.573 --> 00:21:16.132
You shouldn't be here.

293
00:21:16.375 --> 00:21:17.866
You know you're gonna die.

294
00:21:18.077 --> 00:21:19.705
Only not today.

295
00:21:29.088 --> 00:21:31.853
Good news: No dead puppies.

296
00:21:32.024 --> 00:21:36.120
Bad news: I think it's time to use
that word nobody wants to use.

297
00:21:36.295 --> 00:21:38.127
So we have a cult.

298
00:21:39.498 --> 00:21:40.989
You sure this man wasn't Jordy?

299
00:21:41.167 --> 00:21:43.659
Height. weight. nothing
matched. It was someone else.

300
00:21:43.836 --> 00:21:47.466
We weren't supposed to find this
place. This is where they met and planned.

301
00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:51.907
- I think Carroll...
- Carroll is using Poe's work as a religion.

302
00:21:52.111 --> 00:21:54.637
He's speaking to people
through Gothic Romanticism.

303
00:21:54.814 --> 00:21:59.684
There's a pathology to today's
Internet techno-bred minds.

304
00:21:59.852 --> 00:22:02.822
It's created a new
vacancy in our humanity.

305
00:22:04.256 --> 00:22:07.192
Find the ones with
additional disorders...

306
00:22:07.359 --> 00:22:08.827
jackpot.

307
00:22:09.128 --> 00:22:14.863
Enter a handsome. charismatic
man who can touch them...

308
00:22:15.768 --> 00:22:18.897
make them feel their
lives for the first time.

309
00:22:19.071 --> 00:22:20.937
He conditions them.

310
00:22:22.241 --> 00:22:27.043
The only way to
truly live. is to kill.

311
00:22:28.380 --> 00:22:30.542
Or some crap like that.

312
00:22:33.352 --> 00:22:35.548
I run the Bureau's
alternative religion unit.

313
00:22:35.955 --> 00:22:37.355
Did I not mention that?

314
00:22:37.957 --> 00:22:40.950
Cults are my specialty.

315
00:22:46.699 --> 00:22:48.224
- Hey. we online?
- Yeah.

316
00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:51.234
- Is it secure?
- A little slow. but I got us into the board.

317
00:22:51.604 --> 00:22:52.697
It's untraceable.

318
00:22:52.872 --> 00:22:53.965
You check the news yet?

319
00:22:54.173 --> 00:22:55.937
Yeah. we're everywhere. man.

320
00:22:57.309 --> 00:22:58.902
That's the photo
that they pick of me?

321
00:22:59.078 --> 00:23:00.137
I hate that picture.

322
00:23:00.312 --> 00:23:02.474
Did you get it running?
What's up with Jordy?

323
00:23:02.681 --> 00:23:06.448
He hasn't e-mailed yet. but they did
find three girls at the sorority house.

324
00:23:06.619 --> 00:23:07.819
A score for the village idiot.

325
00:23:09.188 --> 00:23:11.089
Paul. will you watch
Joey for a few minutes?

326
00:23:11.257 --> 00:23:12.589
I can do it.

327
00:23:14.493 --> 00:23:15.927
Be a good wingman. Paul.

328
00:23:25.137 --> 00:23:26.901
Are you sure he's straight?

329
00:23:27.072 --> 00:23:29.564
Because he is acting
like a jealous little bitch.

330
00:23:30.209 --> 00:23:32.405
He just feels like
the third wheel.

331
00:23:33.212 --> 00:23:35.647
And for a long time. it
was just me and him.

332
00:23:35.814 --> 00:23:37.009
Now everything's changed.

333
00:23:37.216 --> 00:23:39.276
Well. he needs to adjust.

334
00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:44.156
This is what Joe wanted.

335
00:23:45.624 --> 00:23:47.752
What do you think?

336
00:23:48.494 --> 00:23:51.987
My mom says it makes
me look like a boy...

337
00:23:52.464 --> 00:23:54.126
or a girl who doesn't like boys.

338
00:23:54.300 --> 00:23:57.327
Your mother doesn't
understand you. She never has.

339
00:23:58.170 --> 00:24:02.164
I like it very much.
Emma. It's beautiful.

340
00:24:05.678 --> 00:24:07.544
What if I told you...

341
00:24:07.746 --> 00:24:11.308
that I might know someone
else who might like it too?

342
00:24:13.385 --> 00:24:17.254
A guy? You wanna set me up?

343
00:24:18.390 --> 00:24:20.325
I think you'd like each other.

344
00:24:21.160 --> 00:24:23.288
I don't know.

345
00:24:26.031 --> 00:24:30.492
I love our visits. They
mean the world to me.

346
00:24:31.904 --> 00:24:35.636
But I think you need
to make more friends.

347
00:24:35.808 --> 00:24:39.336
Go out. have some fun.

348
00:24:50.689 --> 00:24:52.021
Emma?

349
00:24:55.928 --> 00:24:57.521
Hi.

350
00:25:00.599 --> 00:25:02.659
Joe said you'd be my type.

351
00:25:04.403 --> 00:25:05.871
What's your type?

352
00:25:09.208 --> 00:25:10.870
Special.

353
00:25:26.025 --> 00:25:28.290
I got eight. maybe nine
different handwritings.

354
00:25:28.460 --> 00:25:30.019
I want analysis on each one.

355
00:25:30.195 --> 00:25:32.426
- How many prints?
- Four clean. Several partial.

356
00:25:32.598 --> 00:25:34.260
Our masked man
was living here too.

357
00:25:34.433 --> 00:25:35.560
Unmade bed. Fresh food.

358
00:25:35.734 --> 00:25:38.863
There's Internet upstairs.
He took his laptop and server.

359
00:25:49.148 --> 00:25:51.083
Is it okay that I'm
happy about this?

360
00:25:51.250 --> 00:25:56.712
I mean. I know divorce is not
a happy subject. but I'm happy.

361
00:25:56.922 --> 00:25:58.754
Well. it's a new
chapter in your life.

362
00:25:59.958 --> 00:26:04.589
Joe's been sentenced. He's gone.
I think you deserve some happy.

363
00:26:04.763 --> 00:26:08.097
All right. well. here's to
being a single lady again.

364
00:26:09.935 --> 00:26:10.959
That's depressing.

365
00:26:13.939 --> 00:26:15.305
Kiss me.

366
00:26:17.776 --> 00:26:20.644
Yeah. you heard
me. I'm single. so...

367
00:26:22.748 --> 00:26:27.448
- Are you sure you want me to kiss you?
- I'm very sure. Been sure for a long time.

368
00:26:27.820 --> 00:26:29.755
Well. if you're sure.

369
00:26:29.922 --> 00:26:32.687
Unless. are you
sure? Because if...

370
00:26:32.891 --> 00:26:36.453
I don't think first kisses are
supposed to have this much discussion.

371
00:26:36.628 --> 00:26:38.620
- Takes the spontaneity out.
- Kind of does.

372
00:26:38.797 --> 00:26:40.493
Did I just ruin our first kiss?

373
00:26:40.666 --> 00:26:42.635
I think it can be salvaged.

374
00:27:07.493 --> 00:27:09.860
So we got an update from Rick.

375
00:27:10.295 --> 00:27:11.729
The FBI found Emma's house.

376
00:27:13.232 --> 00:27:16.031
What do you mean they found
Emma's house? Was Jordy there?

377
00:27:16.201 --> 00:27:19.330
No. Rick was. but he got
away. He wants Emma to call.

378
00:27:19.505 --> 00:27:20.973
Why?

379
00:27:21.440 --> 00:27:23.136
Because she's in
charge. remember?

380
00:27:23.742 --> 00:27:26.405
I'm not trusted with
the important things.

381
00:27:26.578 --> 00:27:32.484
That's not true. all right? She's
just been here for longer. that's all.

382
00:27:32.651 --> 00:27:35.917
You guys need to stop this thing
that you got going. It's awkward.

383
00:27:36.088 --> 00:27:38.956
Awkward for whom. man?

384
00:27:39.658 --> 00:27:43.254
I'm fine. It's just. I don't
get what you see in her.

385
00:27:43.595 --> 00:27:46.064
You're way out of
her league. man.

386
00:27:49.101 --> 00:27:51.229
I think she's amazing.

387
00:28:02.781 --> 00:28:08.084
So tell me. Jacob.
what do you do?

388
00:28:10.522 --> 00:28:12.855
Currently. I am in between jobs.

389
00:28:13.125 --> 00:28:14.184
Hmm.

390
00:28:14.359 --> 00:28:16.726
Well. you're too pretty to work.

391
00:28:17.362 --> 00:28:18.887
Mom.

392
00:28:19.298 --> 00:28:21.062
I can't believe
you two are dating.

393
00:28:24.436 --> 00:28:27.531
Your daughter is the most
amazing woman I know.

394
00:28:28.373 --> 00:28:29.397
Hmm.

395
00:28:30.642 --> 00:28:33.612
Hmm. so you like the no-fuss
plain Janes? That's sweet.

396
00:28:33.779 --> 00:28:35.407
Most boys don't.

397
00:28:50.295 --> 00:28:51.888
You did it.

398
00:29:02.040 --> 00:29:03.133
You really did it.

399
00:29:37.709 --> 00:29:38.870
Who are all these women?

400
00:29:40.045 --> 00:29:42.742
All names of women in
Poe's life and work that died.

401
00:30:13.078 --> 00:30:15.809
Female. She's been dead a while.

402
00:30:15.981 --> 00:30:17.313
Mother?

403
00:30:17.683 --> 00:30:19.083
Buried in the wall.

404
00:30:19.251 --> 00:30:21.618
"Black Cat." "Cask
of Amontillado."

405
00:30:21.787 --> 00:30:23.813
Classic Poe.

406
00:30:33.999 --> 00:30:37.265
Call the Matthews' residence.
Make sure Claire Matthews is safe.

407
00:30:46.678 --> 00:30:50.206
She's safe. The house is secure
and there's no sign of entry.

408
00:30:54.453 --> 00:30:57.389
- Anything?
- Denise's real name is Emma Hill.

409
00:30:57.589 --> 00:31:00.457
She's been visiting Joe in
prison. She is part of this...

410
00:31:00.625 --> 00:31:02.526
but. no. we didn't find her.

411
00:31:22.547 --> 00:31:27.110
Hey. fellas. Eyes up.
huh? You're on watch.

412
00:31:27.352 --> 00:31:29.514
Coffee break. for God's sake.

413
00:31:50.275 --> 00:31:52.005
All good.

414
00:32:07.292 --> 00:32:09.420
Nine different
handwritings were found.

415
00:32:09.928 --> 00:32:15.026
We matched all our suspects.
but five remain unidentified.

416
00:32:15.734 --> 00:32:19.933
M.E. has confirmed that dead body
is Emma's mother. Sharon Cooper.

417
00:32:20.105 --> 00:32:22.233
Still no ID on the masked man.

418
00:32:22.941 --> 00:32:27.276
Jordy. a disorganized killer with a
low IQ. How does he just disappear?

419
00:33:31.042 --> 00:33:32.510
What are those?

420
00:33:32.677 --> 00:33:34.009
Blueprints.

421
00:33:35.080 --> 00:33:37.481
They were on the wall
of the nanny's house.

422
00:33:39.050 --> 00:33:40.916
That's the closet
they took her through.

423
00:33:42.687 --> 00:33:45.213
That's the garage where
the officer was killed.

424
00:33:50.328 --> 00:33:52.058
Wait a minute.

425
00:33:52.230 --> 00:33:53.425
That's Claire's basement.

426
00:33:59.204 --> 00:34:00.502
Run back! Cover!

427
00:34:00.672 --> 00:34:02.197
Go. run back! Cover back!

428
00:34:06.177 --> 00:34:07.873
Don't shoot. I'm unarmed.

429
00:34:08.413 --> 00:34:09.711
It's you.

430
00:34:10.615 --> 00:34:12.880
Finally. We've
been waiting for you.

431
00:34:13.552 --> 00:34:15.953
Keep them out.
Keep everybody out.

432
00:34:16.121 --> 00:34:18.386
Get back. Everyone
back. Get back!

433
00:34:19.391 --> 00:34:20.825
Okay. Jordy.

434
00:34:21.927 --> 00:34:23.088
They're gone.

435
00:34:23.895 --> 00:34:25.295
It's just us.

436
00:34:25.463 --> 00:34:27.091
Okay?

437
00:34:27.933 --> 00:34:29.458
Can I shut the door?

438
00:34:29.634 --> 00:34:31.125
That's good. You shut the door.

439
00:34:43.415 --> 00:34:44.747
Take the gun from her head.

440
00:34:44.916 --> 00:34:47.442
- I have to kill her.
- No. you don't.

441
00:34:47.919 --> 00:34:49.387
And you have to watch.

442
00:34:49.654 --> 00:34:51.122
Those are the rules.

443
00:34:51.656 --> 00:34:53.215
Or. uh...

444
00:34:53.491 --> 00:34:54.982
Or what?

445
00:34:55.160 --> 00:34:56.423
Or you have to kill me.

446
00:34:59.064 --> 00:35:00.794
I'm not sure I'm ready to die.

447
00:35:00.966 --> 00:35:03.629
Jordy. nobody has to die.
Joe doesn't want her to die.

448
00:35:03.802 --> 00:35:05.293
Yes. he does.

449
00:35:05.470 --> 00:35:07.632
And he chose me to do
it. Not anyone else. me.

450
00:35:07.806 --> 00:35:10.776
This is my chapter. And I
can write it any way I want to.

451
00:35:10.942 --> 00:35:12.604
Okay. I'll tell you what.

452
00:35:13.178 --> 00:35:14.373
Why don't we call him?

453
00:35:15.647 --> 00:35:19.084
We can call him. We can ask him.

454
00:35:19.250 --> 00:35:20.809
I have his number.

455
00:35:22.921 --> 00:35:26.414
There's a phone. Right
over there by the bed.

456
00:35:30.462 --> 00:35:31.760
Get an ambulance!

457
00:35:40.405 --> 00:35:44.843
- The storm windows were padlocked.
- He had a key. The nanny gave it to him.

458
00:35:45.010 --> 00:35:46.290
He was dressed as a cop.

459
00:35:46.344 --> 00:35:48.973
He hid under one of the
a.c. units nobody knew about.

460
00:35:49.180 --> 00:35:51.809
Except the nanny
who gave it to him.

461
00:35:51.983 --> 00:35:54.418
- How were we supposed to know?
- It's your job.

462
00:35:56.621 --> 00:35:57.714
Okay. listen up.

463
00:35:57.922 --> 00:36:01.882
If you are not a federal agent. I want
you out of this house. Understand?

464
00:36:02.060 --> 00:36:03.790
Come on. Let's go.

465
00:36:30.088 --> 00:36:31.647
What's up?

466
00:36:32.991 --> 00:36:34.015
She's a strong woman.

467
00:36:34.893 --> 00:36:36.088
She has to be.

468
00:36:36.661 --> 00:36:40.757
The prison guard's in surgery. He'll be
fine. We'll question him once he's conscious.

469
00:36:40.965 --> 00:36:42.524
I wanna see Joe.

470
00:36:43.668 --> 00:36:45.728
So you can break his other hand?

471
00:37:13.364 --> 00:37:15.299
They don't trust
me alone with you.

472
00:37:16.901 --> 00:37:18.062
How's the hand?

473
00:37:20.038 --> 00:37:21.802
Have you slept?

474
00:37:22.774 --> 00:37:23.901
You look tired.

475
00:37:24.409 --> 00:37:26.935
<i>It's important you
take care of yourself.</i>

476
00:37:27.112 --> 00:37:28.808
<i>Preserve your strength.</i>

477
00:37:29.314 --> 00:37:33.911
I've made a few requests. Nothing
scandalous. just a couple of books.

478
00:37:34.085 --> 00:37:35.519
Claire almost died tonight.

479
00:37:35.787 --> 00:37:38.086
I like to read before bed.

480
00:37:39.124 --> 00:37:41.025
Calms the mind. helps me sleep.

481
00:37:41.593 --> 00:37:43.425
She almost died.

482
00:37:43.595 --> 00:37:45.621
The woman you profess to love.

483
00:37:45.797 --> 00:37:49.097
Yeah. but she didn't. I
was hoping you'd save her.

484
00:37:50.101 --> 00:37:53.663
A heroic victory by the leading
man that cements the love story.

485
00:37:53.838 --> 00:37:55.466
What if I hadn't
arrived in time?

486
00:37:55.640 --> 00:37:58.474
Well. that's what makes
the story so unpredictable.

487
00:37:59.043 --> 00:38:03.105
You gotta toughen up. Ryan.
You're dealing with depraved minds.

488
00:38:03.281 --> 00:38:05.273
Sick and twisted.

489
00:38:05.950 --> 00:38:10.251
No. Jordy was a mere puppy...

490
00:38:10.488 --> 00:38:13.185
compared to some of the
games I have in store for you.

491
00:38:21.633 --> 00:38:22.794
Why you doing this. Joe?

492
00:38:23.268 --> 00:38:25.362
The challenge. Ryan...

493
00:38:25.570 --> 00:38:26.970
accept it.

494
00:38:27.505 --> 00:38:29.701
We've barely even started.

495
00:38:29.874 --> 00:38:34.175
I have so many
surprises waiting for you.

496
00:38:34.646 --> 00:38:37.946
<i>And how long do you think you
can keep this up behind bars?</i>

497
00:38:38.449 --> 00:38:39.883
<i>What's the end game?</i>

498
00:38:40.084 --> 00:38:42.883
That's a question the hero
must answer. I'm sorry. Ryan...

499
00:38:43.087 --> 00:38:46.956
you really are going to have
to do some of the work yourself.

500
00:38:48.526 --> 00:38:53.226
Jordy was the first step
in your return to form.

501
00:38:53.398 --> 00:38:54.991
You saved the day.

502
00:38:55.166 --> 00:38:58.864
How does it feel
to be victorious?

503
00:38:59.103 --> 00:39:00.366
To kill the villain?

504
00:39:06.678 --> 00:39:08.306
I didn't kill him.

505
00:39:10.248 --> 00:39:13.184
Jordy's alive and well. He's
in a cell right down the hall.

506
00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:17.052
That wasn't part
of the plan. was it?

507
00:39:19.224 --> 00:39:20.817
No.

508
00:39:21.693 --> 00:39:25.630
It doesn't matter.
He knows nothing.

509
00:39:25.830 --> 00:39:28.766
Man's a half-wit.

510
00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:31.094
Extremely short shelf life.

511
00:39:31.269 --> 00:39:33.932
I'll be sure and tell him
that when I speak to him.

512
00:39:35.173 --> 00:39:36.471
Sleep tight.

513
00:39:51.155 --> 00:39:52.282
It's good.

514
00:39:52.457 --> 00:39:54.255
Okay. thanks.

515
00:40:00.064 --> 00:40:02.932
You don't have to stay here.
We can take you someplace else.

516
00:40:03.101 --> 00:40:04.296
Where?

517
00:40:07.405 --> 00:40:09.431
You should get some sleep.

518
00:40:11.109 --> 00:40:12.168
Don't go.

519
00:40:15.613 --> 00:40:17.775
I don't trust anyone but you.

520
00:40:20.585 --> 00:40:22.486
I'm not going anywhere.

521
00:42:54.338 --> 00:42:55.931
Call my editor.
See if you can't...

522
00:43:03.448 --> 00:43:04.848
What the hell? Hey!
